{
  "text": "The factor N 1 is a normalization factor and it's used to simplify the analysis of the system of Fig. 1 , because it pulls the power of the phasors' vector, j X to unity, as it is shown in the main literature of [CITATION_1] . The weight vector components w j0 , w j1 ,\u2026., w jN-1 are updated at each sampling time index j in accordance to the well-known LMS adaptation rule,",
